<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
<table bgcolor="white" align="right"> <tr><td bgcolor="white"><table>
<caption><font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">Race Prep, Step 1: No Beard!</font></caption>
<tr><td>
 <IMG SRC="../psfull/nobeard.jpg">
</td></tr></table> </td></tr></table>
</font>
</p>
<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
I did the Richard Petty Driving Experience in Florida.  Walt Disney World
Raceway in Orlando, Florida, to be precise.  It was early June, and was
rather hot in Florida.
</font>
</p>
<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
So, I shaved my beard off, partly because of the heat, and also
because the full beard, such as you saw in the previous
picture can get tangled in a helmet chin strap, especially if someone
else tightens it.
</font>
</p>
<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
Besides, I eventually reasoned, to have a true
Richard Petty Driving Experience, one really should have sideburns similar
to the ones Richard Petty wore at the height of his racing career in the
mid-1970's.
</font>
</p>
<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
So, after we arrived in Florida, I began shaving my own beard off.
</font>
</p>
<p>
<font face="Comic Sans MS, Lucida Sans, Helvetica">
This was the first step.  Even though I first cut the beard hair short
with scissors, I still wore out an amazing number of Trac II blades just
getting to this stage.
</font>
</p>
</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table>
<br>


